  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Currently the [5s RPC timeout is hardcoded](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/d60cfd2604a4615078696da20d474828be65ab70/internal/ethapi/api.go#L975). If we were to add a command line param to configure it, where should the config live?\r\n- [P2P Config](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/d8ff53dfb8a516f47db37dbc7fd7ad18a1e8a125/node/config.go#L109) as RpcTimeout (applies to all of http/ws/etc)\r\n- [Top-level backend config](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/d60cfd2604a4615078696da20d474828be65ab70/eth/api_backend.go#L44)\r\n- Somewhere else?\r\n\r\nAs for why this might be useful, I'm bootstrapping initial contract state in another process using a call() via local RPC. Fetching a uint256[1000000] memory via a call() takes just under 5s, usually.",
